Why removing this?

38:24-38:35
Wed Sep 16 12:23:42 2015 +0000
Author: Vladimir Marko <1018108@85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889>
Parent: 89fb8b33_8181bcf0
UUID: 64211e85_884a579a
Bytes: 449
Because ValueObject prevents even placement new which is used to actually construct elements in containers. Previously we used objects that were never constructed, just relied on the memory being zeroed by the ArenaAllocator. Instead of constructing a Location object, we used to copy one to the uninitialized storage.

I'm thinking about adding the placement operators new/delete to DISALOW_ALLOCATION to actually allow this use of the ValueObject.

